CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 18, 1960, pg. B7 reads: "8. The Cuban Tourist Commission booth was beseiged [sic]...curious visitors as hostesses Ida Mae Grant and Jewel Clark glorified...sures and beauty of a Havana vacation."
TitMainTitle: Eleven women, including Ida Mae Grant and Jewel Clark, two men, and young girl, standing in the Cuban Tourist Commission booth in Syria Mosque for the 1960 Courier-WAMO Home-A-Rama
